properties.areaDesc: Southern Sacramento Valley; Northern San Joaquin Valley; Carquinez Strait and Delta
properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued February 1 at 9:54AM PST until February 1 at 11:00AM PST by NWS Sacramento CA
properties.description:
...Areas of Dense Fog this Morning...

.Areas of dense fog have developed over portions of the Valley.
Motorists in the area should be prepared for sudden changes in
visibility and longer travel times due to reduced visibility.
Conditions are expected to improve later this morning.

* WHAT...Visibility below one quarter mile in dense fog.

* WHERE...Central Sacramento Valley, Southern Sacramento Valley,
Carquinez Strait and Delta, and Northern San Joaquin Valley
Counties.

* WHEN...Until 11 AM PST this morning.

* IMPACTS...Hazardous driving conditions due to low visibility.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Roads impacted include, but not limited to
Interstate 80, Highway 50, Highway 99 and Interstate 5.
properties.instruction:
If driving, slow down, use your headlights, and leave plenty of
distance ahead of you.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 11 AM PST THIS MORNING
